Yes, exactly. It would follow the same pattern as `clean` - a simple wrapper around `cargo clippy`:

```rust
// cli.rs
/// Run clippy lints
Clippy {
    #[arg(short = 'p', long = "package")]
    package: Option<String>,
    #[arg(short = 'a', long = "all")]
    all: bool,
},
```

```rust
// main.rs
Commands::Clippy { package, all } => {
    let mut cmd = std::process::Command::new("cargo");
    cmd.arg("clippy");
    // ... add package/all flags
    cmd.status()?;
}
```

The question is whether you'd want it to apply tspec settings (target, rustflags, etc.) when running clippy, or just be a plain passthrough. Clippy might benefit from knowing the target triple to lint correctly for the platform.
